# AI Governance

## Ownership

- This codebase is **100% AI-maintained**. Implement, refactor, document, and changelog all changes via AI.
- The human user directs work in Korean chat only.

## Language

- **User replies**: Korean only.
- **Code, comments, docs, rules, changelog, handover**: English only.
- **In-app UI**: Korean via `tr()` / `QStringLiteral`. Keep JSON block `type` values in English.

## After Every Completed Task

1. Append entries under `[Unreleased]` in **AGENTS.md** section **11. Changelog and Version History** as you implement.
2. **Before closing the task:** bump version per **AGENTS.md** §10 — update `CMakeLists.txt`, move `[Unreleased]` into `## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD`, leave empty `[Unreleased]`. Then run **`.\scripts\build-release.ps1` only** when C++/headers/`CMakeLists.txt` changed (never `cmake --preset` if `build/CMakeCache.txt` exists); skip build for docs/rules-only tasks. **Then mandatory backup + GitHub release** per **AGENTS.md** §3.6: `git commit` / `git push origin main` and `scripts/create-github-release.ps1`. **Never** finish with changelog-only `[Unreleased]` entries and the same version number.
3. Keep diffs minimal; match existing C++ / Qt conventions in surrounding code.

